.TH GRAFANA-UTIL-DATASOURCE-MODIFY 1 "2026-04-03" "grafana-util 0.7.4" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
grafana\-util\-datasource\-modify \- Modify one live Grafana datasource through the Grafana API.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B grafana-util datasource modify [\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Modify one live Grafana datasource through the Grafana API.
.PP
Use this when a datasource already exists and you need to update its URL, auth, JSON payload, or other live settings.
.SH COMMON OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-uid
datasource UID to modify.
.TP
.B \-\-set\-url
replace the datasource URL.
.TP
.B \-\-set\-access
replace the datasource access mode.
.TP
.B \-\-set\-default
set or clear the default datasource flag.
.TP
.B \-\-basic\-auth, \-\-basic\-auth\-user, \-\-basic\-auth\-password
update basic auth settings.
.TP
.B \-\-user, \-\-password, \-\-with\-credentials, \-\-http\-header
update supported request settings.
.TP
.B \-\-tls\-skip\-verify, \-\-server\-name
update TLS\-related settings.
.TP
.B \-\-json\-data, \-\-secure\-json\-data, \-\-secure\-json\-data\-placeholders, \-\-secret\-values
update structured fields and secrets.
.TP
.B \-\-dry\-run, \-\-table, \-\-json, \-\-output\-format, \-\-no\-header
preview output controls.
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Modify one live Grafana datasource through the Grafana API.
.EX
grafana-util datasource modify --url http://localhost:3000 --basic-user admin --basic-password admin --uid prom-main --set-url http://prometheus-v2:9090 --dry-run --json
.EE
.PP
Modify one live Grafana datasource through the Grafana API.
.EX
grafana-util datasource modify --profile prod --uid prom-main --set-default true --dry-run --table
.EE
.SH SEE ALSO
\fBgrafana-util\fR(1),
\fBgrafana-util-datasource\fR(1)
